  "notes": "Azalea Town is the 2nd gym city in Johto. The town's identity revolves around its spiritual relationship with Slowpoke. The Slowpoke Well (northeast, tile 31,7) is a sacred landmark believed to summon rain. Team Rocket's presence here (cutting Slowpoke tails for profit) is the player's first major Team Rocket confrontation. Kurt is the sole craftsman of Apricorn-based Poke Balls in the region — his house is northwest. The Charcoal Kiln provides the Farfetch'd that unlocks HM01 Cut via the Ilex Forest quest. The west exits at tile(2,10) and tile(2,11) lead to the Ilex Forest Azalea Gate, which requires Cut to traverse. Connection offset from prompt: WEST to Route34 at offset -18 refers to gate connection; EAST to Route33 at offset 0."
}
